# SenseL Caldera Linux Lab Rules

- Only act on localhost Docker resources for in-repo automation (Caldera compose, abilities, scripts).
- Phase 3 (HexStrike MCP + Kali) is optional and external: only when the operator explicitly enables it and states authorized lab scope. Default Kali target: `192.168.1.110` on lab LAN — never public IPs, Proxmox, SOC admin, databases, or Tailscale admin.
- Never target public IPs, host network, Docker socket, Proxmox, SOC admin services, databases, or Tailscale admin from repo automation.
- Do not add credential dumping, persistence, privilege escalation, lateral movement, exploitation, reverse shells, payload downloads, ransomware behavior, or external exfiltration.
- Do not use privileged containers.
- All exercises must write structured JSON markers.
- All exercises must have cleanup.
- Before modifying Caldera deployment logic, inspect the checked-out Caldera version and do not invent endpoints.
- Keep secrets only in `.env`, never commit them.
